#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&katomic; is a fun and educational game built around molecular geometry. It "
"employs a simplistic two-dimensional look at the elements which comprise a "
"molecule. A molecule is disassembled into its separate atoms and scattered "
"around the playing field. The player must reassemble the molecule in order "
"to complete the current level and move up to the next one."
msgstr ""
"&katomic; je zabavna in izobraževalna igra, zgrajena okoli molekularne "
"geometrije. Uporablja poenostavljen dvodimenzionalen pogled na elemente, ki "
"sestavljajo molekulo. Molekula je razstavljena na svoje ločene atome in "
"razpršena po igralnem polju. Igralec mora znova sestaviti molekulo, da "
"dokonča trenutno raven in se premakne na naslednjo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Kako igrati"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "&katomic; main screen"
msgstr "&katomic; glavni zaslon"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Cilj:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reassemble molecules from compound atoms by sliding them around."
msgstr ""
"Ponovno sestaviti molekule iz sestavljenih atomov tako, da jih drsite "
"naokoli."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&katomic; will load level one once you start the game and you can begin "
"playing right away. To see how the molecule you are supposed to make looks "
"like, take a look at the upper right corner. To play, click on an atom. You "
"will see green arrows pointing in the directions where atom can move. To "
"move the atom, click on the desired arrow. When an atom starts moving, it "
"will not stop until it hits another atom or a wall, so make sure you think "
"before you do your next move. You can assemble your molecule wherever you "
"like on the game board, but some places are easier to access than others. "
"When the molecule is assembled, you can move to the next level."
msgstr ""
"&katomic; bo naložil prvo stopnjo, ko začnete igro in lahko začnete igrati "
"takoj. Če želite videti, kako je videti molekula, ki naj bi jo naredili, "
"poglejte v zgornji desni kot. Za igranje kliknite na atom. Videli boste "
"zelene puščice, ki kažejo v smeri, kjer se atom lahko premika. Če želite "
"premakniti atom, kliknite na želeno puščico. Ko se atom začne premikati, se "
"ne bo ustavil, dokler ne zadene drugega atoma ali stene, zato premislite, "
"preden naredite naslednjo potezo. Svojo molekulo lahko sestavite kjerkoli na "
"igralni plošči, vendar so nekatera mesta lažje dostopna kot druga. Ko je "
"molekula sestavljena, se lahko premaknete na naslednjo stopnjo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Pravila igre, strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules"
msgstr "Pravila igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game pieces can only move in one direction at a time."
msgstr "Igralne figure se lahko premikajo samo v eno smer naenkrat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once an atom begins moving it will not stop until it meets either a wall or "
"another piece."
msgstr ""
"Ko se atom začne premikati, se ne bo ustavil, dokler ne naleti na steno ali "
"drug kos."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The only way to progress to the next game level is to complete a current "
"one. Once a player completes a certain level the game automatically switches "
"to the next one, thus <quote>uncovering it</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Edini način za napredovanje na naslednjo stopnjo igre je dokončanje "
"trenutne. Ko igralec dokonča določeno stopnjo, igra samodejno preklopi na "
"naslednjo in jo tako <quote>odkrije</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "A player can only switch between the levels which have been uncovered."
msgstr "Igralec lahko preklaplja le med stopnjami, ki so bile odkrite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The game progress is automatically saved every time an adjacent level is "
"reached, and will be reloaded the next time application is started."
msgstr ""
"Napredek v igri se samodejno shrani vsakič, ko je dosežena sosednja raven, "
"in se bo znova naložil ob naslednjem zagonu aplikacije."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Always review the complete molecule using the reference screen before making "
"any moves."
msgstr ""
"Vedno preglejte celotno molekulo z referenčnim zaslonom, preden naredite "
"kakršen koli premik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, study the play field and plan your moves. Remember, once a piece is "
"moved it may not be possible to return it into the starting position."
msgstr ""
"Nato preučite igralno polje in načrtujte svoje poteze. Ne pozabite, da ko je "
"kos premaknjen, ga morda ne bo več mogoče vrniti v začetni položaj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Think through your every move and try to visualize the trajectory piece will "
"follow once a directional arrow is clicked."
msgstr ""
"Premislite o vsakem svojem gibu in poskusite vizualizirati pot, ki ji bo kos "
"sledil, ko kliknete smerno puščico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the keyboard to move pieces make sure that the desired piece is "
"selected. If a wrong atom is marked as selected, use the &Tab; key to switch "
"between the pieces until you reach a desired one."
msgstr ""
"Ko uporabljate tipkovnico za premikanje figur, se prepričajte, da je želena "
"figura izbrana. Če je kot izbran napačen atom, uporabite &Tab; tipko za "
"preklapljanje med deli, dokler ne dosežete želenega."

